This system provides a comprehensive view of the employee lifecycle from hiring through development, helping HR teams make data-driven decisions about their workforce across multiple business locations.
What it does:
Employee Management:

Tracks employee personal information, contact details, positions, departments, and employment status
Manages employee documents (resumes, passports, photos)
Monitors employee work experience and tenure
Performance & Development:

KPI tracking - measures employee performance against targets (sales, customer service, etc.)
SWOT analysis - evaluates employee strengths, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats
Personal Development Plans (PDP) - sets and tracks skill development goals
Motivation mapping - identifies what motivates each employee (money, career growth, recognition, etc.)
Onboarding Process:

Manages new employee integration with stages from "awaiting start date" to "completed"
Tracks onboarding tasks, responsible trainers, and progress
Monitors onboarding timelines and identifies delays
Employee Events & Achievements:

Records professional achievements, awards, conflicts, and warnings
Maintains a timeline of significant employee events
Documents HR comments and supporting evidence

